  "research_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">The <strong>Sympotic Satire Fragments</strong> are a collection of fourteen fragmentary passages attributed to the Hellenistic poet Lycophron of Chalcis. Preserved solely as quotations in later authors, primarily Athenaeus’s <strong>Deipnosophistae</strong>, these verses represent a work of satyric or sympotic poetry distinct from Lycophron’s extant tragedy <strong>Alexandra</strong>. The fragments reflect their convivial context and satirical style, containing references to dining practices and foods, comic or burlesque treatments of mythological figures, and aetiological explanations for rituals and customs. The work survives entirely through this indirect transmission, having been quoted by antiquarians such as Athenaeus, who flourished in the late second or early third century CE. Modern editions, including the <strong>Poetae Comici Graeci</strong>, compile these fragments, though the original work’s full scope and precise format remain unreconstructable. These pieces illustrate the diversity of Hellenistic poetry beyond major surviving texts. Their preservation highlights later scholarly interest in banquet culture and mythological lore, while their attribution to Lycophron connects them to the Alexandrian literary milieu and the scholarly curation of comic and satyric drama.</p>\n</div>",
  "rows": [
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 2.1",
      "text": "[spk_σιλ]ΣΙΛ. παῖδες κρατίστου",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 2.2",
      "text": "πατρὸς ἐξωλέστατοι, ἐγὼ μὲν ὑμῖν, ὡς ὁρᾶτε, στρηνιῶ· δεῖπνον γὰρ οὔτ’ ἐν Καρίᾳ, μὰ τοὺς θεούς, οὔτ’ ἐν Ῥόδῳ τοιοῦτον οὔτ’ ἐν Λυδίᾳ[ln_5]κατέχω δεδειπνηκώς· Ἄπολλον, ὡς καλόν ἀλλὰ κυλίκιον ὑδαρὲς ὁ παῖς",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 2.3",
      "text": "περιῆγε",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 2.4",
      "text": "τοῦ πεντωβόλου, ἀτρέμα",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 2.5",
      "text": "παρεξεστηκός· ὅ τ’ ἀλιτήριος καὶ δημόκοινος ἐπεχόρευε δαψιλής[ln_10]θέρμος, πενήτων καὶ τρικλίνου",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 2.6",
      "text": "συμπότης",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 3.1",
      "text": "ὡς ἐκ βραχείας δαιτὸς ἡ βαιὰ κύλιξ αὐτοῖς κυκλεῖται",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 3.2",
      "text": "πρὸς μέτρον, τράγημα δέ ὁ σωφρονιστὴς πᾶσιν ἐν μέσῳ λόγος",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 4.1",
      "text": "πολλάκις",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 4.2",
      "text": "συνόντας αὐτοὺς[ln_staging]ἐπὶ πλεῖον ὁ ὄρνις κατελάμβανε[ln_3]τὴν ἕω καλῶν 〈––〉 τοῖσι δ’ οὐδέπω κόρος",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 5.1",
      "text": "[ln_1]ἀλλ’ ἡνίκ’ ἂν μὲν ᾖ πρόσω τὸ κατθανεῖν, Ἅιδης",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 5.2",
      "text": "ποθεῖται",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 5.3",
      "text": "τοῖς δεδυστυχηκόσιν· ὅταν δ’ ἐφέρπῃ κῦμα λοίσθιον βίου, τὸ ζῆν",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
